ifJnx.name: ifJnx

revisions.description: New Layer2 Policer Counters Added to ifJnxTable for MX Series only
Added new OIDs Crc and Fcs Erros. Added new Trap ifJnxErrors
New error counters added to ifJnxTable
New objects ifHCIn1SecRate and ifHCOut1SecRate added

ifJnx.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
ifJnx.description: The MIB modules extends the ifTable as defined in IF-MIB.

ifJnxTable.name: ifJnxTable
ifJnxTable.description: A list of Juniper's extension to the interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber. This table contains additional objects for the interface table.

ifJnxEntry.name: ifJnxEntry
ifJnxEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular interface.

ifIn1SecRate.name: ifIn1SecRate
ifIn1SecRate.description: The number of bits per second (bps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next higher (sub-)layer.

ifIn1SecOctets.name: ifIn1SecOctets
ifIn1SecOctets.description: The number of octets per second (Bps, Bytes per second), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next higher (sub-)layer.

ifIn1SecPkts.name: ifIn1SecPkts
ifIn1SecPkts.description: The number of packets per second (pps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next higher (sub-)layer.

ifOut1SecRate.name: ifOut1SecRate
ifOut1SecRate.description: The number of bits per second (bps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next lower (sub-)layer.

ifOut1SecOctets.name: ifOut1SecOctets
ifOut1SecOctets.description: The number of octets per second (Bps, Bytes per second), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next lower (sub-)layer.

ifOut1SecPkts.name: ifOut1SecPkts
ifOut1SecPkts.description: The number of packets per second (pps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next lower (sub-)layer.

ifHCIn1SecRate.name: ifHCIn1SecRate
ifHCIn1SecRate.description: The number of bits per second (bps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next higher (sub-)layer. This object is a 64 bit version of ifIn1SecRate.

ifHCOut1SecRate.name: ifHCOut1SecRate
ifHCOut1SecRate.description: The number of bits per second (bps), delivered by this (sub-)layer to its next lower (sub-)layer. This object is a 64 bit version of ifOut1SecRate.

ifJnxInErrors.name: ifJnxInErrors
ifJnxInErrors.description: Errors: The sum of the incoming frame aborts and FCS errors.

ifJnxInFrameErrors.name: ifJnxInFrameErrors
ifJnxInFrameErrors.description: Framing Errors: The number of input packets which were misaligned.

ifJnxInQDrops.name: ifJnxInQDrops
ifJnxInQDrops.description: Drops: The number of packets dropped by the input queue of the I/O Manager ASIC.

ifJnxInRunts.name: ifJnxInRunts
ifJnxInRunts.description: Runts: Frames received that are smaller than the runt threshold.

ifJnxInGiants.name: ifJnxInGiants
ifJnxInGiants.description: Giants: Frames received that are larger than the giant threshold.

ifJnxInDiscards.name: ifJnxInDiscards
ifJnxInDiscards.description: Policed Discards: Frames that the incoming packet match code discarded because they were not recognized or of interest.

ifJnxInHslCrcErrors.name: ifJnxInHslCrcErrors
ifJnxInHslCrcErrors.description: HS Link CRC Errors: The number of CRC errors on the high-speed links between the ASICs responsible for handling the router interfaces while receiving packets.

ifJnxInHslFifoOverFlows.name: ifJnxInHslFifoOverFlows
ifJnxInHslFifoOverFlows.description: HS link FIFO overflows: The number of FIFO overflows on the high-speed links between the ASICs responsible for handling the router interfaces.

ifJnxInL3Incompletes.name: ifJnxInL3Incompletes
ifJnxInL3Incompletes.description: L3 incompletes: The number of incoming packets that fail Layer 3 sanity checks of the header.

ifJnxInL2ChanErrors.name: ifJnxInL2ChanErrors
ifJnxInL2ChanErrors.description: L2 channel errors: the number of incoming packets for which the sofware could not find a valid logical interface.

ifJnxInL2MismatchTimeouts.name: ifJnxInL2MismatchTimeouts
ifJnxInL2MismatchTimeouts.description: L2 mismatch timeouts: The count of malformed or short packets that cause the incoming packet handler to discard the frame as unreadable.

ifJnxInInvalidVCs.name: ifJnxInInvalidVCs
ifJnxInInvalidVCs.description: Invalid VCs: Number of cells that arrived for a nonexistent virtual circuit.

ifJnxInFifoErrors.name: ifJnxInFifoErrors
ifJnxInFifoErrors.description: FIFO errors: The number of FIFO errors in the receive direction as reported by the ASIC on the PIC.

ifJnxBucketDrops.name: ifJnxBucketDrops
ifJnxBucketDrops.description: Bucket drops: Drops due to traffic load exceeding the interface transmit/receive leaky bucket configuration.

ifJnxSramErrors.name: ifJnxSramErrors
ifJnxSramErrors.description: SRAM errors: This counter increments when a hardware error has occurred in the SRAM on the PIC.

ifJnxOutErrors.name: ifJnxOutErrors
ifJnxOutErrors.description: Errors: The sum of the outgoing frame aborts and FCS errors.

ifJnxCollisions.name: ifJnxCollisions
ifJnxCollisions.description: Collisions: The number of output collisions detected on this interface.

ifJnxCarrierTrans.name: ifJnxCarrierTrans
ifJnxCarrierTrans.description: Carrier transitions: The number of times the interface saw the carrier signal transition.

ifJnxOutQDrops.name: ifJnxOutQDrops
ifJnxOutQDrops.description: Drops: The number of packets dropped by the output queue of the I/O Manager ASIC.

ifJnxOutAgedErrors.name: ifJnxOutAgedErrors
ifJnxOutAgedErrors.description: Aged packets: The number of packets that remained in shared packet SDRAM for so long that the system automatically purged them.

ifJnxOutFifoErrors.name: ifJnxOutFifoErrors
ifJnxOutFifoErrors.description: FIFO errors: The number of FIFO errors in the transmit direction as reported by the ASIC on the PIC.

ifJnxOutHslFifoUnderFlows.name: ifJnxOutHslFifoUnderFlows
ifJnxOutHslFifoUnderFlows.description: HS link FIFO underflows: The number of FIFO underflows on the high-speed links between the ASICs responsible for handling the router interfaces.

ifJnxOutHslCrcErrors.name: ifJnxOutHslCrcErrors
ifJnxOutHslCrcErrors.description: HS Link CRC Errors: The number of CRC errors on the high-speed links between the ASICs responsible for handling the router interfaces while transmitting packets.

ifJnxCrcErrors.name: ifJnxCrcErrors
ifJnxCrcErrors.description: CRC Errors: The number of CRC errors

ifJnxFcsErrors.name: ifJnxFcsErrors
ifJnxFcsErrors.description: FCS Errors: The number of FCS errors

ifChassisTable.name: ifChassisTable
ifChassisTable.description: A list of Juniper's extension to the interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber. This table contains additional objects for the interface table to facilitate the identification of interfaces and its mapping into the Chassis MIB tables.

ifChassisEntry.name: ifChassisEntry
ifChassisEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular interface.

ifChassisFpc.name: ifChassisFpc
ifChassisFpc.description: The number of the FPC card on which the interface is located in the chassis. It is the chassis slot in which the FPC card is installed for the specified interface. Although the number is labeled from 0 and up in the chassis, the return value for this object always starts from 1 according to Network Management convention. Therefore, a value of zero means there is no real or physical FPC associated with the specified interface.

ifChassisPic.name: ifChassisPic
ifChassisPic.description: The number of the PIC card on which the interface is located in the chassis. It is the PIC location on the FPC card for the specified interface. Although the number is labeled from 0 and up in the chassis, the return value for this object always starts from 1 according to Network Management convention. Therefore, a value of zero means there is no real or physical PIC associated with the specified interface.

ifChassisPort.name: ifChassisPort
ifChassisPort.description: The number of the port on the PIC card on which the interface is located in the chassis. It is the port number on the PIC card for the specified interface. Although the number is labeled from 0 and up in the chassis, the return value for this object always starts from 1 according to Network Management convention. Therefore, a value of zero means there is no real or physical port associated with the specified interface.

ifChassisChannel.name: ifChassisChannel
ifChassisChannel.description: The channel identifier for the specified interface if and only if it is part of a channelized interface. Although the channel is numbered from 0 and up in the interface naming, the return value for this object always starts from 1 according to Network Management convention. For the interface which could not be channelized, this object returns zero.

ifChassisLogicalUnit.name: ifChassisLogicalUnit
ifChassisLogicalUnit.description: The logical unit number of the specified interface. It is the logical part of the interface that is configured on the physical or channel part if any. Although the logical unit number is numbered from 0 and up in the interface naming, the return value for this object always starts from 1 according to Network Management convention. For the interface which is really a physical device, this value returns zero.

ifChassisPicIndex.name: ifChassisPicIndex
ifChassisPicIndex.description: The index or indices for the Chassis MIB tables. This is the instance index which keys into the jnxContentsTable in Chassis MIB. For example, it could return an octet string of '8.1.2.0' - meaning a PIC ('8', first digit) at FPC slot 0 ('1-1', second digit minus one if nonzero) PIC number 1 ('2-1', third digit minus one if nonzero) port number whatever (fourth digit currently unused) - which in turn could be plugged in by NMS directly after any MIB objects in the jnxContentsTable, say 'jnxContentsDescr.8.1.2.0', so NMS could get that PIC object for the specified interface. This object is valid only for those interfaces having real and physical PIC cards. Otherwise, it returns an octet string of four zeros '0.0.0.0.'

ifJnxErrors.name: ifJnxErrors
ifJnxErrors.description: A ifJnxErrors notification is sent when the value of ifJnxCrcErrors or ifJnxFcsErrors increases.
